    {
      "id": "f93bd0563a80c01dda36bcc1ae1dd1fe61c76290",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 298,
        "name": "Jeff Mahoney",
        "email": "jeffm@suse.com",
        "username": "jeffm"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-20 15:43:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nWhy was the static file list portion of the patch removed? Getting rid of lustre.files was half of the benefit of it.\n\nWRT globs, using broad globs like %{_libdir}/* for packages is a bad idea because if a portion of the build failed in a clean way (like via a missing optional dependency), there's no way to notice. You'll just end up with a package that is missing files rather than a package that fails to build because of missing files.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "fe4cec080f684334c213cd9e4340daa7e0130b92",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 298,
        "name": "Jeff Mahoney",
        "email": "jeffm@suse.com",
        "username": "jeffm"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-20 15:43:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n*getting rid of most of lustre.files.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "334be45f9e8aa12e1b5cc73217880028f202ae75",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-20 16:58:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWelcome back.The reason for not removing the file list was the POST_SCRIPT section which handles both lustre.files and lustre.test. Can dynamic file list be used in that case?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b3bff25d33d2fe4a40bf37436fd4d19d03fb6119",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 298,
        "name": "Jeff Mahoney",
        "email": "jeffm@suse.com",
        "username": "jeffm"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-20 21:48:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt's possible to do the POST_SCRIPT stuff without a file list but that's not what I was after. The first section of dumping filenames into lustre.files can be moved below the %files section and still use lustre.files for what's leftover. That's what my original patch did.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
